In regard to #TheWall: After some back-and-forth votes and vetos, President @realDonaldTrump emergency declaration stands. The president has done what he can to secure the border, notwithstanding Congress’ willingness to work with him.

In regard to supporting small business: I have been in the trenches and understand what it is like to build a business. As a #SmallBusiness owner, I know that you never clock out. I am here to advocate for you! Stay tuned for the second part of our small business tour in Oct!

In regard to #2ndAmendment rights: I am the cosponsor of a bill that would allow states to recognize concealed carry laws from the individual’s home state, so that crossing state lines does not put people in legal danger for carrying their firearm with a permit.

In regards to the Born Alive Act: The Act would require medical personnel to actually try to save a baby’s life if it is born alive during a botched abortion attempt. This is an issue of right or wrong. What we do about an issue like this says a lot about who we are as a nation.

In regard to congressional term limits: I am unashamedly supportive of this. I am the cosponsor of a 12-year term limit bill to bring fresh ideas to congress and deter those who come to DC with preservation of power in mind.

In regard to cost of medical care: I am glad to be working with @SenRickScott to combat the issue of surprise medical billing. I’ve experienced this issue myself and we have to do better. Times of emergency should not equate to surplus medical feels.

In regard to the impeachment inquiry on @realDonaldTrump : It’s clear to me that there is a presumption of the president’s guilt. We’ve gone from collusion, to obstruction and now this. It’s time to serve our constituents, not our political motives.
I’ll be kicking off my tele-townhall in about ten minutes! Stay tuned here for updates if you aren’t able to join us. #FL #FL15
